sub_title: Coordinator Seaweed Markets at North Sea Farmers | MSc Sustainable Development
summary:
I am a Geoscientist with a Master degree in Sustainable Development & I’m as interested about environment/natural sciences as about society/politics/people/culture.

With 12 years of experience living internationally, I have worked in Brazil, Venezuela, France, Germany and the Netherlands, where I have decided to settle down (for now, at least). My interest in different languages and cultures have always helped me communicate and contribute effectively with people from different backgrounds. 

I love working with diverse people, preferably in interdisciplinary groups, and I am a strong believer in teamwork!
